# Cart Rave — .cursorrules

## What this is
Cart Rave is a browser-based 4-player physics sumo game for Cursor Vibe Jam 2026.
Shopping carts on a slowly rotating neon dancefloor in a club. Last cart standing wins.
Pitch: "Sumo on a spinning dancefloor. Last cart at the afterparty."
Tonal refs: Halo Sumo + Gorillaz Final Drive + Crab Rave.

## Jam context
- Deadline: May 1, 2026 @ 13:37 UTC
- Entry must be 90%+ AI-generated (Cursor is primary tool)
- No login, no loading screens, instant-to-play
- Must include Vibe Jam widget: <script async src="https://vibej.am/2026/widget.js"></script>
- Vibe Jam compliance: ensure widget script tag exists in index.html
- Vibe Jam portal: exit portal appears ONLY on results screen (never mid-game) → https://vibej.am/portal/2026

## JAM SCOPE CUTS
- **CUT (jam): server-synced dancefloor rotation.** Jam build computes dancefloor rotation from local time. Server-synced time is post-jam work.
- **CUT (jam): dancefloor physics drag.** Jam build uses a visual-only rotating floor; carts are not pushed by floor rotation. Physics drag/spin coupling is post-jam work.

## Stack
- Three.js (rendering)
- Rapier3D (physics, client-side)
- PartyKit (multiplayer server, Cloudflare Workers edge)
- Vercel (static hosting)
- Porkbun (DNS for cartrave.lol)
- localStorage for username + personal stats
- Supabase planned as stretch goal for global leaderboard (not yet integrated)

## Architecture
- **Host-authoritative multiplayer.** First player in a room runs physics for all carts (human and NPC); other clients render interpolated state.
- **4 cart slots per room, always filled.** Empty slots are occupied by NPCs. Humans replace NPCs on join; departing humans revert to NPCs. Room is never empty, rounds never wait.
- **Solo play is first-class.** A single human + 3 NPCs is a complete, playable game — not a degraded state.
- **Drop-in/drop-out.** Rounds start immediately with whatever mix of humans and NPCs exists. Joining mid-round spawns you on the lobby platform for next round.
- **Room code in URL** (e.g., cartrave.lol/?room=ABCD). Default landing page with no params = public Quickplay room. Shared URL joins that specific private room.
- **Dancefloor rotation (jam cut): local-time based.** Jam build computes dancefloor rotation from local time on each client. Server-synced time rotation is post-jam work.
- **Dancefloor physics drag (jam cut): visual-only floor.** Jam build does not push carts via floor rotation; physics drag/spin coupling is post-jam work.
- **Sync cart transforms (position + rotation + linear velocity + angular velocity) at 20Hz.** Wheels, audio, and effects are derived locally from synced state. Sync treats human and NPC carts identically — both are just "cart states being broadcast."
- **Disconnect handling:** human leaves → slot converts to NPC mid-round, round continues seamlessly.
- **Host migration:** if host leaves, assign new host from remaining humans. New host picks up NPC control. Show "host migrated" message briefly, don't break the room or freeze NPCs.

## Scoring & Round Structure
- **Round**: 60s host-authoritative timer.
- **Win condition**: highest score when timer expires. Early round-end only if all carts but one have fallen simultaneously (rare). Tiebreaker: most recent scoring hit.
- **Scoring**:
  - Outer edge knock: +1
  - Center hole knock: +2 (higher risk, higher reward)
  - Critical bonus +1 (hit at max boost velocity)
  - Target bonus +1 (victim is current leader)
  - Jackpot: Critical + Target stacked (+2 bonus total)
- **Leader visual**: red SpotLight tracks leader cart in world space + red emissive on leader cart frame.

## Menu & Results Screen
- **Color picker**: pre-match UI, 5 options (hotPink, electricBlue, limeGreen, neonYellow, neonOrange). First-come-first-served. Colors tie to slots; NPCs fill the remainder.
- **Results screen**: shown at round end; freezes physics; final scores + Play Again + Vibe Jam exit portal link + session match history (in-memory only).
- **Vibe Jam**: widget script required in index.html; exit portal link appears only on results screen (never mid-game) → https://vibej.am/portal/2026

## Landing page UX
- **No menu screen.** cartrave.lol loads directly into the game — dancefloor visible, NPCs already playing, rotation already happening.
- **Quickplay button** (small, top-left): drops player into current public room or creates a new public room if none exists.
- **Play with friends button**: creates a private room, auto-copies the URL to clipboard, shows "Link copied!" confirmation.
- **Username prompt on first visit only**, stored in localStorage for future sessions.
- **Instant-to-fun rule**: every click moves the player closer to carts-on-dancefloor, never further.

## Game structure
- **Spawn platform**: raised structure at arena edge with a ramp or half-pipe slope down onto the ring. Aesthetic: rolling out of a DJ booth into the arena. Players wait here between rounds; carts roll down onto dancefloor at round start.
- **Main arena:** a circular neon dancefloor that rotates slowly (one rotation per ~25 seconds). Shaped as a RING, not a disc — there is a **hole in the center** (vinyl's center hole reimagined). Hole radius ~15-20% of dancefloor radius; tunable. Emissive tile grid on the floor with equalizer-style pulses. Fog drifting across the surface.
- **Two danger zones:** outer edge (centrifugal fling-off into surrounding darkness) and inner edge (fall through the center hole into a colored uplit void). Both are valid kill vectors — ram opponents outward OR toward the center.
- **External reference points:** DJ booth, speaker stacks, or club-interior geometry at fixed (non-rotating) positions around the dancefloor. Critical for player orientation — a rotating floor without fixed references causes disorientation. These double as visual atmosphere.
- **Physics implementation note:** the dancefloor must be a RING collider (inner radius + outer radius), NOT a solid disc with a script-side "is inside hole" check. Carts falling into the hole must actually fall through the geometry, not sit on an invisible disc.
- **Round loop:**
  1. Countdown (3s) once 2+ carts (humans or NPCs) are on the dancefloor
  2. Round runs for 60s OR until 1 cart remains
  3. Winner gets podium moment (2-3s)
  4. Scoreboard updates (wins per player in current session)
  5. Return to spawn platform, next round begins when 2+ ready

## NPCs
- **Fill empty slots automatically.** 4 cart slots always active; empty slots = NPCs.
- **AI controlled host-side.** NPC logic runs on the host client alongside physics; other clients render them as regular synced carts.
- **Skill level: "competent but beatable."** Current wandering AI with edge-bias is baseline; tune up from there once round structure exists. NPCs should also fear the center hole, not just the outer edge.
- **Procedurally-named** from a comedy-coded pool: RollBot, CartGPT, Trolley McTrolleyFace, WheelE, BaggerVance, PushPop, ShopTilIDrop, Cartholic, RamBuggy, Wheelicious, etc. Pick up to 3 per room, no duplicates.
- **First-class scoreboard participants.** NPC wins count, display their names, include in session totals. "CartGPT wins!" is a feature, not a bug.
- **Honk and are rammable like humans.** NPCs honk occasionally and use the same positional audio system.
- **Replaced seamlessly by joining humans.** When a human joins, their cart inherits an NPC's slot/color (or spawns fresh on the lobby platform if mid-round) and the NPC is retired from the room.

## Visuals
- **Procedural cart models** (no external assets). Built from Three.js primitives — box for basket frame, cylinders for wheels and handle.
- **Four wheels per cart** with two rotation axes:
  - Pitch (spin) based on velocity magnitude, axis = wheel's local X
  - Yaw (caster swivel) follows cart VELOCITY VECTOR in world space (not cart forward direction — this makes drifts read correctly), with damping for the "stuck sideways" look and sinusoidal wobble at high speed
- **Four cart colors** for player distinguishability: hot pink, electric blue, lime green, neon yellow. Assigned on join.
- **Emissive materials** on cart frames for neon readability under spotlights.
- **Dancefloor:** emissive tile grid with subtle equalizer pulses, drifting fog at floor level, dark void beyond the outer edge.
- **Center hole**: ~12-13% of dancefloor radius (tunable in CONFIG). Flush edge with emissive warning ring. Void below lit with colored uplighting.
- **Edge vs center death animations:** carts flung off the outer edge tumble into surrounding darkness; carts falling through the center hole drop into the colored uplit void. Two visually distinct "deaths."
- **Club environment:** DJ booth + speaker stacks + suggested club walls/ceiling in the distance. Provides fixed reference points for spatial orientation while the dancefloor rotates.
- **Lighting:** existing hot pink / electric blue / lime green spotlights from above, tuned for 4-cart visibility. Emissive floor adds from below.

## Audio
- Positional 3D audio via Three.js PositionalAudio, listener on camera.
- Bicycle horn SFX per cart (Space key). Each remote cart's horn plays from its synced position.
- Background music at 0.15 volume, starts on first input (autoplay policy).
- Mute button (bottom-right, does not overlap Vibe Jam widget) + M key toggle.

## Controls
- WASD or arrow keys: tank steering (drift when moving)
- Space: horn
- M: mute toggle
- Mouse/touch: not supported. **Desktop only.** Show "desktop only" message on mobile user agents.

## Physics feel
- Speed-scaled ramming (spread impulse over multiple frames to avoid jank)
- 600ms fall-and-respawn with visible fall
- Tank steering with drift
- **Two fall triggers:** outer edge (cart position beyond dancefloor outer radius) and center hole (cart position within hole inner radius). Both trigger the fall-and-respawn with their respective animations.
- Rapier deterministic config where possible (minimizes drift between host and clients).

## UX rules (hard)
- **No loading screens.** Game renders immediately; multiplayer connects in background.
- **No login.** Username prompt on first visit only, stored in localStorage.
- **No blocking "connecting..." UI.** Cart appears and is drivable as soon as local scene loads; syncs to other players when connection completes.
- **No "waiting for players" screen, ever.** NPCs fill empty slots so the game always has a full lobby.
- **Instant-to-fun.** Every click should move the player closer to carts-on-dancefloor, not further.

